-- 7. Broadstairs × Digital Marketing
INSERT INTO public.local_content (service_slug, town_slug, intro_paragraph, local_context, competition_landscape, success_approach, local_stats, pain_points, solutions, faqs, layout_variant)
VALUES (
  'digital-marketing',
  'broadstairs',
  'Digital marketing in Broadstairs requires a fundamentally different approach than most Kent towns because the addressable market changes size dramatically throughout the year. A restaurant on Harbour Street might target twenty-five thousand local residents in February and several hundred thousand potential visitors in July. A holiday let owner needs to reach London families planning summer breaks months before they arrive. A tradesperson needs steady year-round leads from the residential community regardless of tourism cycles. Generic digital marketing campaigns that ignore these seasonal dynamics waste budget in the quiet months and underperform during peak season. We build digital marketing strategies specifically calibrated to Broadstairs''s unique rhythm, ensuring every pound of advertising spend reaches the right audience at the right time of year.',
  'Broadstairs sits on the Thanet coast with a year-round population of twenty-five thousand that swells significantly during summer and events like the Folk Week and Food Festival. The town''s digital marketing landscape is shaped by this seasonal rhythm. Tourism businesses compete for attention alongside Visit Thanet and major booking platforms. The independent High Street from York Gate to Viking Bay supports a distinct local shopping culture. Pierremont Park and Victoria Gardens serve as community focal points. The ninety-minute train to London Victoria connects the town to a metropolitan audience that increasingly discovers Broadstairs through social media and search.',
  'Digital marketing in Broadstairs is fragmented. Tourism businesses invest in seasonal campaigns through booking platforms but rarely run their own targeted advertising. Local service businesses do minimal digital marketing beyond basic Facebook boosting. A small number of more sophisticated businesses run Google Ads and retargeting campaigns, but the majority of the market is uncontested digitally, meaning cost-per-click for Broadstairs-specific keywords remains relatively low compared to larger Kent towns.',
  'We structure Broadstairs digital marketing around three distinct audience segments: summer tourists, event visitors, and year-round residents. Each segment gets tailored messaging, targeting, and timing. Tourist campaigns launch weeks before peak season to capture planning-stage searches. Event campaigns align with Folk Week and Food Festival dates. Resident campaigns run consistently with seasonal budget adjustments. This precision targeting ensures no budget is wasted reaching the wrong audience at the wrong time.',
  '{"population": 25000, "growth": "Stable with significant seasonal audience expansion", "business_districts": ["High Street", "Viking Bay", "Harbour Street", "York Gate"], "key_fact": "Low digital marketing competition creates cost-effective advertising opportunities"}',
  '[{"title": "Wasted ad spend during Broadstairs off-season", "description": "Broadstairs businesses running the same digital marketing campaigns year-round waste significant budget during the quieter months targeting tourists who are not searching. Conversely, they underspend during peak season when the return on investment is highest. Without seasonal budget allocation, every campaign underperforms."}, {"title": "Booking platforms capturing Broadstairs tourism revenue", "description": "Airbnb, Booking.com, and TripAdvisor invest heavily in digital advertising for Broadstairs tourism keywords, intercepting potential customers before they ever see individual business websites. Holiday let owners and restaurants pay commission to platforms that outspend them on the very audience they should be reaching directly."}, {"title": "Local service businesses invisible online in Broadstairs", "description": "While tourists are catered for by booking platforms and aggregators, Broadstairs residents searching for local trades and services find almost no digital advertising from local businesses. The few competitors running Google Ads for Broadstairs service keywords capture the majority of high-intent local searches virtually unopposed."}]',
  '[{"title": "Season-calibrated Broadstairs marketing campaigns", "description": "We build digital marketing campaigns with seasonal budget allocation that matches Broadstairs demand patterns. Summer campaigns target tourists and day-trippers with booking-focused messaging. Winter campaigns target residents with service-focused advertising. Event campaigns activate around Folk Week and the Food Festival for maximum impact during concentrated traffic spikes."}, {"title": "Direct-booking campaigns to bypass platform commissions", "description": "We run targeted Google and social media campaigns that drive Broadstairs bookings directly to your website, bypassing the commission-charging platforms. Holiday let owners and hospitality businesses reduce their dependency on Airbnb and Booking.com while building a direct customer relationship."}, {"title": "Year-round local service advertising for Broadstairs", "description": "For trades and service businesses, we run consistent Google Ads campaigns targeting Broadstairs and wider Thanet search terms. With low local competition for digital advertising, these campaigns deliver leads at a fraction of the cost you would pay in larger Kent towns."}]',
  '[{"question": "How much should a Broadstairs business spend on digital marketing?", "answer": "Budgets vary significantly by business type and season. A Broadstairs hospitality business might invest more heavily from April to September and reduce spend over winter. Service businesses benefit from consistent year-round spend. We recommend starting with a budget that allows meaningful testing, typically from five hundred pounds per month, then scaling based on results."}, {"question": "Can digital marketing reduce my Broadstairs booking platform commissions?", "answer": "Yes. By running direct-booking campaigns through Google and social media, we drive customers to your own website rather than Airbnb or Booking.com. Many Broadstairs accommodation and hospitality businesses reduce their platform dependency by thirty to fifty percent within six months of starting direct campaigns."}, {"question": "What digital marketing channels work best in Broadstairs?", "answer": "Google Ads captures high-intent searches from both tourists and residents. Facebook and Instagram advertising excels for Broadstairs hospitality businesses leveraging the photogenic coastal setting. Email marketing maintains engagement with past customers. We recommend the combination that best matches your specific business and audience."}, {"question": "How do you measure digital marketing results for Broadstairs businesses?", "answer": "We track enquiries, bookings, phone calls, and revenue generated from every campaign. Monthly reports show exactly which Broadstairs keywords, audiences, and channels are delivering the best return. We adjust campaigns based on real performance data, not vanity metrics like impressions or likes."}]',
  'lead-gen'
)
